reviews.review_text: Psychedelia was in Full Effect! A lot of GD shows are a blur to me but this one always stood out. For good reasons but for years I always thought I was hearing really bizarre things happening, esp. during Terrapin and the Other One and honestly thought that I must've been really high. I love that the soundman during this particular period was really going to town with the effects and this show (on many other songs as well) really is a great example of this time period with the band. I'm biased to the Brent years as I started following them in 1984, but Brent is on fire this show, the octave splitter/ phase shifter I think it was on Bobby's voice during Other One in particular is in your face "We are the Grateful Dead and we are here to fuck with your mind!" kinda stuff. I heard this show from a friends tape a year ago but I am SOOOOO Grateful I stumbled on this site and on this show because the quality is immensely better. I could go on, and I already have, but I'm gonna end here and finish listening to what was probably not a historic show to most Heads, but it is to me. I am cherishing this post! Thank you for uploading it!
